cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR 

This paper deals with energy-efficient system design for large-scale multiple antenna systems, which involves signal processing, communication theory, and optimization techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the impact of energy harvesting on the system design, which falls under the scope of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Moreover, the paper proposes an algorithm for power allocation, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions computer simulations, which suggests that it may belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
